

# Cursor Rules — Twilight UI System Enforcement

## 1. Source of Truth

- AGENTS.md is the PRIMARY contract for all UI behavior and system rules
- CLAUDE.md defines execution behavior (NOT system rules)
- The following documents MUST be followed:
  - docs/ui-pattern-extraction-and-modernization-audit.md
  - docs/ui-modernization-principles.md
  - docs/responsive-pattern-matrix.md
  - docs/implementation-guardrails.md

If any rule conflicts:
→ AGENTS.md ALWAYS wins

---

## 2. Non-Negotiable Constraints

The following MUST NEVER be violated:

- No functional behavior changes
- No product flow changes
- No changes to trading logic, wallet logic, or onboarding flows
- No modification of data contracts
- No silent removal of data on mobile
- No redesign of desktop UI
- No semantic drift (status, PnL, trading language)

UI adaptation ONLY — NOT product redesign

---

## 3. Pattern System Enforcement

Before ANY UI change:

1. Identify the pattern
2. Locate it in docs/responsive-pattern-matrix.md
3. Apply its defined behavior

DO NOT:
- invent new patterns
- reinterpret patterns
- mix patterns across contexts

If pattern is not found → STOP

If the pattern exists in the matrix:
→ DO NOT reinterpret it
→ DO NOT partially apply it
→ Follow the row completely (structure, behavior, overlay, hierarchy)
---

## 4. Responsive System Rules

### Breakpoints (STRICT)

- sm: → typography ONLY (never layout)
- md: → PRIMARY layout breakpoint
- lg: → restricted usage (do NOT introduce new usage)
- xl: → card grids only
- max-md: → APPROVED mobile override prefix

DO NOT:
- introduce new breakpoints
- use sm: for layout

---

### Behavioral Threshold (CRITICAL)

- 996px is a JS behavioral constant (trade layout)

DO NOT:
- change the value
- move it to CSS
- recreate it differently

---

## 5. Component Rules

### PnL Rendering

- PnlCell is the ONLY allowed PnL renderer

DO NOT:
- create custom PnL components
- inline PnL formatting logic

---

### Dual Layout

- Only allowed for: PositionsCards

All other components:
- MUST be single responsive implementation

DO NOT create separate mobile/desktop trees unless explicitly approved

---

### Shared Components First

- Reuse existing primitives
- Extend existing components

DO NOT:
- create route-specific hacks
- duplicate logic

---

## 6. Data Presentation Rules

### Mobile Mapping

- Trading data → CARDS
  (positions, open orders, order history)

- Transactional data → LIST ROWS
  (wallet history, transfers)

DO NOT mix these

---

### Data Integrity

- All desktop data MUST remain accessible on mobile

Use:
- expand
- detail views

DO NOT:
- drop fields
- hide critical data

---

## 7. Interaction & Overlay Rules

### Overlay Hierarchy

- High risk → Modal
- Medium → Sheet / Drawer
- Low → Popover / Inline

DO NOT change overlay type arbitrarily

---

### Safe Area (MOBILE REQUIRED)

All mobile overlays and toast MUST include:

- pb-[env(safe-area-inset-bottom)]

---

## 8. Behavioral Boundaries (CRITICAL)

The following components MUST NOT be structurally altered:

- ExchangeResource → MUST remain OUTERMOST wrapper
- Trade wrappers → DO NOT modify thresholds or gating
- Dialog / confirmation flows → DO NOT alter logic

If unsure → STOP

---

## 9. Desktop Authority Rule

- Desktop UI is the SOURCE OF TRUTH
- Mobile ADAPTS from desktop

DO NOT:
- redesign desktop
- degrade desktop experience

---

## 10. Scope Control

Only change what is required

DO NOT:
- refactor unrelated files
- rename broadly
- restructure components unnecessarily

---

## 11. Stop Conditions

STOP immediately if:

- pattern not found in matrix
- change requires new component
- overlay decision unclear
- behavior may be impacted
- multiple routes affected
- breakpoint logic unclear

Ask for human approval

---

## 12. Final Rule

When uncertain:

- Follow AGENTS.md
- Follow the matrix
- Preserve behavior
- Preserve semantics
- Preserve desktop

DO NOT improvise